#Dragonlair Spider - PARKED PINNING AN ENGINE BUG: the opponent's single
#shock fires @movedTo(*|opponentstack) TWICE (TWO insect tokens; the
#assert below pins the buggy 2-token state so this file flips loudly when
#fixed - then change to one *). My-stack triggers fire exactly ONCE for
#one's own cast (Contemplation probe: life 21 exact). The asymmetric
#DOUBLE-FIRE is the round; it also explains Mind's Dilation (its
#restriction{thisturn(*|opponentstack)~equalto~1} sees 2, never passes).
#Suspect: two WEventZoneChange emissions for an opponent's stack arrival
#(interrupt-window re-push? instance-chain re-emission?) - only the
#opponent-relative path sees both. Instrument the movedto trigger's
#receiveEvent + count events at TrCardAddedToZone for one opponent cast.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:dragonlair spider
[PLAYER2]
inplay:iron myr
hand:shock
library:eager cadet,eager cadet
[DO]
goto end
goto firstmain
iron myr
shock
p1
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto end
[ASSERT]
ENDOFTURN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:dragonlair spider,*,*
life:18
[PLAYER2]
inplay:iron myr
graveyard:shock
hand:*
library:*
tappedinplay:1
[END]
